Redis (REmote DIctionary Server) is an open-source, in-memory key-value data store, widely used as:
used as cache, data structure serve , no sql database , a message broker


In memory -- > data is stored in the ram- superfast
Data Structures	---> Supports strings, lists, sets, hashes, sorted sets, bitmaps, HyperLogLogs
Atomic
Thread safe
Pub/Sub
TTl Support
Networked Server
Can also save to disks

Use case
caching
session storage
rate limiting -- Track API hits per IP/user
Leaderboard ---> 	Use sorted sets for top scores
Queue Systems	Lists/Streams for task queues
Pub/Sub Chat	Real-time messaging / notification
Distributed Lock -- implements lock with expiration